  "_doc": "Phase-3a demo: every Verilog logic primitive in one scene. Shared inputs `a` and `b` feed each of the eight gate flavours (AND, OR, XOR, NAND, NOR, XNOR, NOT, BUF) plus a 1-bit COMPARATOR. Click VERILOG in the bottom toolbar — the downloaded `.v` shows each gate as a real Verilog primitive instance (`and g_and(...);`, `or g_or(...);`, etc.) with positional ports, plus three `assign` lines from the comparator (==, >, <). NOT and BUF are unary, so they emit two-arg primitives. iverilog parses the result without warnings.",
